# AWS Lambda Python base image CVEs (public.ecr.aws/lambda/python:3.12)
# All in AWS-managed components. Fixes require AWS to publish updated base images.
# Sandbox Lambdas are VPC-isolated with no internet access and no IAM credentials.

# libnghttp2 DoS via malformed HTTP/2 frames. Sandbox can't make HTTP/2 connections.
CVE-2026-27135

# openssl - all require specific protocol usage that Lambda doesn't do:
# CVE-2026-28387: DANE TLSA use-after-free (Lambda doesn't use DANE)
# CVE-2026-28388: delta CRL NULL deref (requires X509_V_FLAG_USE_DELTAS)
# CVE-2026-28389: CMS KeyAgree NULL deref (no CMS processing)
# CVE-2026-28390: CMS EnvelopedData NULL deref (no CMS processing)
# CVE-2026-31790: RSASVE info disclosure (no RSA key encapsulation)
CVE-2026-28387
CVE-2026-28388
CVE-2026-28389
CVE-2026-28390
CVE-2026-31790

# Go stdlib in aws-lambda-rie (Lambda Runtime Interface Emulator)
# Only used for local testing - production Lambda ignores this binary.
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32282
